# Design document rules (studio)

- Every design document MUST contain these sections: Overview, Player Fantasy, Detailed Rules, Formulas, Edge Cases, Dependencies, Tuning Knobs, Acceptance Criteria (adjust titles if the doc type differs, but keep the same intent).
- Formulas must include variable definitions, expected value ranges, and example calculations.
- Edge cases must explicitly state what happens, not only "handle gracefully".
- Dependencies must be bidirectional where systems interact — if system A depends on B, B's doc must mention A.
- Tuning knobs must specify safe ranges and what gameplay aspect they affect.
- Acceptance criteria must be testable — pass/fail observable by QA.
- Balance values must link to their source formula or rationale.
- Write incrementally: skeleton first, then fill sections with user approval between major sections.
